pageContext.claim: “And as you know, Polish Americans came out in droves. They voted in the last election, and I was very happy with that result. So I just want to thank you, and I want to thank them.”
pageContext.analysis: The president is greatly exaggerating here. While some people provide anecdotal evidence that suggests Trump enjoyed more support from Polish Americans, we found no correlation between the density of the Polish American population and the 2016 vote. It's even harder to say definitely that they had a higher turnout than in past years.
